				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">A sad day for EQ<a name="60098"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 2 04 4:58 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I am kind of suprised this has not been posted here already, but then again maybe it is on all your server boards.
<br />

<br />
Sinzan of guild &lt;Mirage&gt; (of the CCH Flash Movie fame) has left EQ. As a parting gift he has posted one last touching movie as a goodbye to his friends on EQ.
<br />

<br />
This will mean more to the older EQ players than the newer generation. For me it brought back a lot of memories; of friends long gone, adventures past, and times when EQ was truely an adventure into the unknown.
<br />

<br />
*Sigh*
<br />

<br />
Anyway, the link is here:
<br />

<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://home.att.ne.jp/surf/mirage/sayonara_norrath3.html">Sinzan's Farewell</a>
<br />

<br />
Guild Mirage's website with the other movies (including the infamous 'CCH movie' can be found here:
<br />

<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://www.guildmirage.com">Guild Mirage</a>
<br />

<br />
A sad bard, 
<br />

<br />
Adropt
<br />
</span></td>
