			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A sad day for EQ<a name="60162"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 3 04 6:05 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I friggin cried watching this thing, I kid you not.
<br />

<br />
So many memories.  I was never guilded with Sinzan or even on the same server, but the memories are the same. 
<br />

<br />
I miss so much.  I miss the tunnel.  I miss a single HQ bear pelt being worth a week's farming.  I miss seeding Crushbone mobs with stuff from Infected Paw.  I miss the druid ring in WC.  I miss SK back when SK meant something more then getting a peg cloak for an alt.  I miss all those bridges and all those rivers and I miss the crowds outside the bank in NFP being so thick it lagged me out.  I miss the hoards of smiths that hung around the forges in FP and Qeynos, and banded armor could be custom bought 24-7.  1p per AC. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
I miss giving a crap that lockjaw had popped, running in terror from spec trains in Oasis, the sheer awe of watching a group bring down a hill giant, Vox and Naggy jumping on my head, but most of all I miss the people that left the game when frustration over PoP flags made them all, one by one, click cancel account.
<br />

<br />
Here's a toast to Sinzan and what his films represent, to all my cartoon brothers and sisters that got the monkey off their backs.  I hope you're safe, I hope you're well.
<br />

<br />
Dlandridel Cadence
<br />
Maestro of Grey Hawke
<br />
Karana Server
<br />

<br />
 </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
