			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A sad day for EQ<a name="60166"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 3 04 6:58 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>My first character was a halfling cleric.  I had no idea he was supposed to be wisdom based.  I had a rl friend that was a wood elf druid who got a port to Rivervale.  We had no idea what we were doing.  We killed stuff in Misty Thicket for a week (that's how long it took to lvl back then) and then made the &quot;big move&quot; to Freeport because that was the place to be.  I remember even giving the guards in WC all the copper I had on me because I thought they'd kill me if I passed without paying, lol.
<br />

<br />
Everytime I hear the howling at night and the other night time sounds, it reminds me of the Rivervale days.  
<br />

<br />
Sometimes I wish it was still like that.  You know, no websites with guides showing you step by step how to do something.  In away, it was fun figuring it out yourself.  
<br />

<br />
Getting to 20 and getting your surname was a great milestone and took a long time to get there... now it can be done in a day.  
<br />

<br />
Saving up copper pieces to buy your lvl 1 spells was a real challange.  The only people to sell to was the vendors and charisma wasn't an issue because I didn't know it affected the prices then.
<br />

<br />
Someone was always selling through /auction from the tunnel in EC.  &quot;Selling a bag of armor, first torch, pst to look..&quot;
<br />

<br />

<br />
Ah, the good old days.  I miss them :(</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
