				<td colspan="2"><span>My first toon was a half elf druid, and I had no idea I needed wis. A friend of mine got me into the game and I must have died about 15 times in Qeynos hills from those d*mn Dread Corpses, I didn't understand how to con or anything hehehe I didn't even figure out how to cast spells till I was level 3. I remember being a guide for people with my bard and taking them from QH to FP or RM, I loved to travel and the world was so huge it scared the crap out of all of us. Once I got used to the routes I made a bundle taking people from here to there, but I'll never forget the stuff that stood out like the first time I zoned into WK and got attacked and killed by a werewolf I almost crapped my pants. It took me weeks to get to lvl 20 and I did it all in the Karanas, I remember being at the reaver hill in EK and dinging 20 for the first time, surname and all. I was pretty sure I could take on Broon at that point so I tried it and died horribly, losing my level in the process hehe. I remember dying from one shot of crag spider poison, running around freaking out because I couldn't find a heal. HHK.... don't get me started.
<br />
  I remember someone telling me that all the gypsy camps turned into werewolves at night and I didn't go near them for months lol.
<br />
I just about had a heart attack the first time I ever killed a giant, and I couldn't stop smiling when I killed my first Ice Giant, MAN was everfrost huge!
<br />
Good times man...
<br />
