				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A sad day for EQ<a name="60194"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 3 04 10:10 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>My very first memory of Everquest was the auto-attack button.  I had read the instructions, and knew that you could hail npcs.  I walked up, tried to talk to the NPC's, and got &quot;loading, please wait&quot;.  I kept doing this for about two hours, trying every NPC I could find.  I finally found a player to talk to, who thought it was funnier than h*ll that I was attacking every NPC and dying every time I had enough time to load.
<br />

<br />
I remember the first time I got a piece of banded armor - in fact, when I was about 5th level (back in 1999, mind you) someone gave me a minotaur axe and bronze arms.  I was invincible, the bane to the fire beetles and gnoll pups of Qeynos.  I still used those well up into my 30's.
<br />

<br />
I remember crossing West Karana to hunt in North karana, and dreading the run every time.  To this day I still go into insta-bored mode whenever I think if West karana.
<br />

<br />
I never thought I'd ever be one of those peole to talk about &quot;the good old days&quot;, especially in regards to a game.  But EQ, pre-Kunark, has made me think of those days.  Bad loot (compared to today), 50th level max, and realizing that the only raid you'll ever go on is Vox, Naggy, or Kedge Keep.</span></td>
