				<td colspan="2"><span>You never know what you've got 'til it's gone.   I am always surprised to see the amazing artists that share this addiction of mine.  I shouldn't be...
<br />

<br />
My favorite EQ memory is one of my favorite all-time memories.  I started playing EQ the day after release and found a regular group of adventurers right away.  We got a few levels in Gfay then headed to BB to fight the gobbies just outside the dwarf city entrance.  When we were all around level 7 or 8, we decided to go on an adventure.  We took the boat to Freeport and started heading to Qeynos.  We made it to High Hold, but we didn't make it out.  That last 30 mins of trying to dodge orcs and gnolls were more intense than the best thriller outta Hollywood.  My wife left fingernail marks in my shoulders while she watched.
<br />

<br />
I've since lost touch with those brave adventurers and my wife refuses to play anything but EQ or EQ2 now.  I will be leaving EQ soon myself (again - for the last time) and I just wish I had had the chance to adventure more with the Sinzan's of the world.
<br />

<br />
Thanks so much for sharing this, Adropt.</span></td>
