				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A sad day for EQ<a name="60574"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 5 04 10:55 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>:)
<br />

<br />
I remember standing on the walls in Steamfont, afraid to death that the Minotaur Hero would spawn, praying he would pass me by.  Running my Clerics butt off to Ak Anon trying to get away.  At the time (Jun-Jul 1999), we thought he was the 3rd hardest NPC in the game.
<br />

<br />
My 1st character, a Ranger, I took all the way from Qeynos to Freeport at level 5.  I remember camping for the night in the little huts I found, convinced that if the mobs didnt peak in the huts, they wouldnt attack me.  I had no idea I was just lucky beyond all compare.
<br />

<br />
Lots of fun in the Orc camps in Greater Faydark at level 7 or so.  I died a lot there.  Always a constant stream of trains heading to the lifts.
<br />

<br />
I remember running from Borxx in RunnyEye.  One day, I saw an SK (I think) tanking Borxx and I was absolutely amazed.  This guy was hitting for upwards of 70 damage a swing.  I had never seen anything like it.  He was going to die, so I spot healed him.  After Borxx died, he let me loot the thing-a-ma-jig that got you the Staff Of The Observers.  Man, that was UBER!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
