			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: A sad day for EQ<a name="60697"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 6 04 10:11 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>My first EQ character was a druid. I had been a hardcore UO player, loved my GM archer fencer healer gal. I asked a friend who had played in the beta with me which class would fit my style. He said a Druid or a Bard.
<br />

<br />
Somewhere around level 35 I saw a Bard charm kiting Hill Giants.
<br />

<br />
I immediately logged off.
<br />

<br />
I have never played another class since. My Bard is ancient. Over 400 days played. She is not some goddess getting phat lewt on flagged zones or planes. She has gear I personally looted from pick up groups. I've done my fair share of raiding and even survived a year of DKP squabbling...Killed many dragons and other PoP nasties, but, never seemed to get much.
<br />

<br />
Never got my epic, could never find a guild that was not &quot;too power obsessed with themselves&quot; to help me get the tendril I needed or Phinny's spine..
<br />

<br />
I held a lot of resentment for never being helped when I needed it. I spent 50% of my career chant kiting crap and 50% in groups doing things they never seen a bard do and well. I have always taken pride in my ability to be a battle commander.
<br />

<br />
I spent over 2 years in DAoC leading raids to nab relics, getting millions of realm points.... playing an Albion minstrel...
<br />

<br />
I always come back to EQ. Today I see things for sale in the bazaar that were god like in 1999. I see hundreds of uber guilds all camping this or that or talking about getting a raid item as if it were easy.
<br />

<br />
I read the description of EQ2 and no.. Bards are not the same there. No game has had a class as utterly gratifying, to me, as the EQ Bard.
<br />

<br />
When EQ finally dies, so will one of the greatest classes ever created.
<br />

<br />
For me, I enjoy playing. I love pick up groups, I will probably never see any god like loot, and am proud of my little Dragonrib Club.
<br />

<br />
My AA count it not in the hundreds, but maybe if I play more it might be. I am looking forward to the Epic 2.0 and hope that Sony realizes the utter disgusting graphics of EQ is what keeps many players away.
<br />

<br />
I've played Lineage 2, Anarachy online, Ac 1 , AC 2 everything. Only my DAoC infiltrator or minstrel comes as close to my EQ Bardess.
<br />

<br />
I don't have Fade and my AC isn't 1650. But I have always loved playing my bard and playing her well.
<br />

<br />
It is sad to see players leave, but real life continues on, and after an endless quest for uber leethood, eventually the emptiness tries to slip in. Only good friends can keep players going, so remember your friends and make their game play as good as it can be.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Myscha the sleddog
Mercede Dominici 65 bard CT</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
